external_knowledge:
- "storm" metaphorically represents the incidents; "tempest" refers to the critical conditions;
- "those caught in the tempest" are the victims; 
- "the identities" refer to their names and ages;
- "the ties that bind them" represent the relationships between the victims;
- "heroic efforts" and "race against time" are metaphors for the actions taken and the response and arrival times of the emergency units.

sql:
SELECT unit_id, COUNT(incident_id) AS TotalIncidents
FROM incidents_emergency_units
GROUP BY unit_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM victims
WHERE age > 50;
